ğŸ¯ What You Need

To allow Dev account to read Prod S3 bucket:

You must configure TWO things:

âœ… IAM Role in Dev account

âœ… Bucket Policy in Prod account

Thatâ€™s it.

ğŸŸ¦ STEP 1 â€” Create IAM Role in DEV Account

In Dev AWS account, create a role:

Example Role Name:
DevIcebergReplicationRole


Attach this IAM policy to it:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "ReadProdBucket",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::prod-bucket",
        "arn:aws:s3:::prod-bucket/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Sid": "FullAccessToDevBucket",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "s3:*",
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::nonprod-bucket",
        "arn:aws:s3:::nonprod-bucket/*"
      ]
    }
  ]
}

What this does:

Read from Prod bucket

Full access to Dev bucket

Cannot write to Prod

ğŸŸ¦ STEP 2 â€” Modify PROD Bucket Policy

Now go to:

Prod Account â†’ S3 â†’ prod-bucket â†’ Permissions â†’ Bucket Policy

Add this statement:

{
  "Sid": "AllowDevAccountReadAccess",
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Principal": {
    "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<DEV_ACCOUNT_ID>:role/DevIcebergReplicationRole"
  },
  "Action": [
    "s3:GetObject",
    "s3:ListBucket"
  ],
  "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:s3:::prod-bucket",
    "arn:aws:s3:::prod-bucket/*"
  ]
}


Replace:

<DEV_ACCOUNT_ID>


with actual Dev account number.

ğŸ” If Prod Bucket Uses KMS Encryption (Very Important)

If objects are encrypted with a KMS key, you must also update the KMS key policy in Prod.

Go to:
Prod â†’ KMS â†’ Key used by S3 â†’ Key Policy

Add:

{
  "Sid": "AllowDevAccountDecrypt",
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Principal": {
    "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<DEV_ACCOUNT_ID>:role/DevIcebergReplicationRole"
  },
  "Action": [
    "kms:Decrypt",
    "kms:DescribeKey"
  ],
  "Resource": "*"
}


If you skip this, youâ€™ll get:

AccessDenied: KMS Access Denied

